header.gameNote: MEAC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - 1st ROUND AT WINSTON-SALEM NC

article.headline: Florida A&amp,M 74, Coppin St. 72
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- Amin Stevens scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Florida A&M hold off Coppin State 74-72 Tuesday night in the first round of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament. The 11th-seeded Rattlers (9-22) trailed 65-59 with 4:36 remaining and went on an 11-3 run behind six points from Avery Moore. Yannick Crowder's free throws put Florida A&M in the lead, 70-68, with 1:02 to play. Logan Wiens' 3-pointer put No. 6 seed Coppin State (14-16) back on top. But Crowder's basket gave the Rattlers back the lead for good with 28 seconds to play. Moore, who was 4 of 5 from 3-point range, finished with 19 points for Florida A&M, which shot 60 percent from long range (12 of 20). The Rattlers will play No. 3 seed Delaware State in the quarterfinals on Thursday. The Eagles were led by Akeem Ellis with 24 points and Tony Gallo with 21.
